# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv. Since it's personal preference, keep it commented out.
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you intend to development in a local sandbox,
#   you might want to ignore Pipfile.lock.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#.pdm-python
#pdm.lock
#pdm.toml

# PEP 582; introduces a layout for class-loading, similar to node_modules
